  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA71-kiḷavi">itu talaivaṉait tōḻi celavaḻuṅkuvittatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante prevents HIM from going.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA71">
<l>            maṉṉāp poruṭpiṇi muṉṉi yiṉṉatai</l>
<l>            vaḷaiyaṇi muṉkainiṉ ṉikuḷaik kuṇartteṉap</l>
<l>            paṉmā ṇiratti rāyiṟ ceṉmeṉa</l>
<l>            viṭuna ḷātalu muriyaḷ viṭiṉē</l>
<l>            kaṇṇu nutalu nīvi muṉṉiṉṟu </l>
<l>            pirital vallirō vaiya cellā</l>
<l>            vakaiyamar nalli lakaviṟai yuṟaiyum</l>
<l>            vaṇṇap puṟaviṉ ceṅkāṟ cēval</l>
<l>            vīḻtuṇai payiruṅ kaiyaṟu muralkuraṉu</l>
<l>            mayilaḷ pulampak kēṭṭoṟum </l>
<l>            pomma lōti peruvitup puṟavē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent2">If she lets go of [you],</l>
<l rend="indent3">she for whom it is suitable that she also lets go of [you],</l>
<l rend="indent2">saying “go”, when you have begged for many times,</l>
<l rend="indent">since you made your friend<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">kulaikku</term>: here a dative instead of a second acc. (the first one and direct object being <term xml:lang="ta">iṉṉatai</term>) – suspicious enough to put prefer the variant with unmarked <term xml:lang="ta">kiḷai</term> "relative"?</note> with bangle-adorned forearms</l>
<l rend="indent">realise<note place="foot">T.V.G. takes <term xml:lang="ta">uṇarttu</term> here as an ipt., which to me does not seem necessary. And as for the root imperative, how to distinguish between the 4th and 11th class if not by adding <term xml:lang="ta">-tt</term>, so that the form is identical with the absolutive?</note> thus, thinking enticed by impermanent wealth,</l>
<l>– if you stand in front of [her and] stroke [her] eyes and forehead,</l>
<l>will you be strong [enough] to separate [from her], sir,</l>
<l rend="indent2">so that [she with] thick hair has great longing,</l>
<l rend="indent4">whenever she hears, while your peacock-woman is lonely,</l>
<l rend="indent4">the voice sounding to end [all] action,</l>
<l rend="indent3">when the red-legged cock of the coloured dove,</l>
<l rend="indent4">that remains on [its] seat inside the good house,</l>
<l rend="indent4">where it has the habit of abiding without going,</l>
<l rend="indent2">calls [its] descending mate?</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
